		<blockquote class="restore">I should add that I spent over an hour tonight customizing this game so it would run on my specced machine and clicking a lot of boxes, over and over, and reloading the game for options settings...and then I sat therr for 45 minutes as the cutscenes chugged along JUST so i could hit &quot;save&quot; and try the game again later when I was less frustrated.<br />
<br />
I'll probably enjoy it, assuming it runs decently with the settings I have, but the massive cutscenes are segacd/32x era levels of bullshit and they need to be amputated from the industry.<br />
<br />
they're like muscle shirts, stretch pants, yoga pants, or corduroy ocean pacific shorts...just because you CAN implement them in your own area of control doesn't mean you should.</blockquote>
	</div>
</li><li class="postbit blockbody" id="post_3">
