		<div class="title">Re: Fuck you, Kingdoms of Amalur</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore">I think some genres of game have decreased in quality, MMORPGs in particular.  Aside from Demon's Souls and Dark Souls and rogue likes, RPGs have largely become movies with little intellect or skill invested in the plot.  Take Skyrim for example, there was some fantastic story here, and very little cut scenes, and it was awesome.  The combat kind of sucked, but the environment was great, and more and more RPGs are implementing non terrible combat mechanics.  However, MMORPGs, aside from being highly derivative and clones of one another, usually have garbage combat mechanics, no story line, and the player is irrelevant to to the outcome.  Due to increased trend to casual appeal the MMO component of the genre has faded such that for all intents and purposes it might as well be a match maker game.  The state is actually even worse than that though as the match maker usually has no skill rating component to it, so players are matched up with garbage, hardly a fun affair aside from the emotional exploitation that occurs in the genre.</blockquote>
	</div>
